blocks.content:
An **array** is a list of values stored in a single variable. Arrays use square brackets `[]`:

```javascript
let fruits = ["apple", "banana", "orange"];
let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
let mixed = ["text", 42, true, null];
```

Each item in an array has an **index** (position). Indexing starts at 0:

```javascript
let fruits = ["apple", "banana", "orange"];
//              0          1           2

console.log(fruits[0]);  // "apple"
console.log(fruits[1]);  // "banana"
console.log(fruits[2]);  // "orange"
```

blocks.starterCode:
// Create an array
let colors = ["red", "green", "blue"];

// Access items by index
console.log(colors[0]);
console.log(colors[1]);
console.log(colors[2]);

// Find the length
console.log(colors.length);

// Create your own array
let numbers = [10, 20, 30, 40];
console.log(numbers[2]);

let fruits = ["apple", "banana"];

// Add items
fruits.push("orange");
console.log(fruits);  // ["apple", "banana", "orange"]

// Add to beginning
fruits.unshift("mango");
console.log(fruits);

// Check length
console.log("Length: " + fruits.length);

// Find index of item
let index = fruits.indexOf("banana");
console.log("Banana is at index: " + index);

// Check if includes item
if (fruits.includes("apple")) {
  console.log("Array contains apple!");
}

blocks.content:
Powerful methods for working with arrays:

```javascript
let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

// map() - transform each item
let doubled = numbers.map(num => num * 2);
// [2, 4, 6, 8, 10]

// filter() - keep items that match
let evens = numbers.filter(num => num % 2 === 0);
// [2, 4]

// find() - get first matching item
let firstEven = numbers.find(num => num % 2 === 0);
// 2

// some() - check if ANY item matches
let hasEven = numbers.some(num => num % 2 === 0);
// true
```

blocks.starterCode:
let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

// Double each number
let doubled = numbers.map(num => num * 2);
console.log(doubled);  // [2, 4, 6, 8, 10]

// Get only even numbers
let evens = numbers.filter(num => num % 2 === 0);
console.log(evens);    // [2, 4]

// Find first even number
let first = numbers.find(num => num % 2 === 0);
console.log(first);    // 2

// Get sum of all numbers
let sum = numbers.reduce((total, num) => total + num, 0);
console.log(sum);      // 15
